<p>She was born in İstanbul in 1960. She completed her primary and secondary education in Austria Trade High School and studied Management at Vienna University of Economics. In 2010, she wrote her second master thesis in Bilgi University Institute of European Union. She worked as at credit marketing at Tekstilbank and as Congress and Seminars Manager at Otari Tours. Currently, she is a member of board at Topkapı Industry A.S. As she thinks that empowering women and youth is the biggest investment to the future, she is a member of board of trustees at Community Volunteers Foundation, a member of board at Austrian High School Alumni Association, a member of ALD Women’s Platform, a member of KAGİDER. She speaks German, English, and French. She is married with two children.</p>